  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-10-12T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Stopping Threats On Pedestrians Act of 2017 or the STOP Act of 2017\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Transportation to establish a program to assist bollard installation projects designed to prevent pedestrian injuries and acts of terrorism in areas utilized by large numbers of pedestrians. Such a project is one that installs raised concrete or metal posts on a sidewalk adjacent to a roadway that are designed to slow or stop a motor vehicle."
  }, 
